<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-05-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-05-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="604" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d604">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">033.3711/77: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Cuban Secretary of State</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Ortiz</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-05-07"><hi rend="italic">May 7,
                                1927</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received 6:20 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>The President of the Republic on returning to Cuba has brought his people
                            the best impressions of the honors and courtesies extended to him while
                            in your country. In the name of the Government and People of Cuba I wish
                            to convey to you our sincere and deepest appreciation.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Rafael Martínez
                            Ortiz</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>